President of France Nicolas Sarkozy and Prime Minister of Italy Silvio Berlusconi meet to discuss what to do about migrants from North Africa who want to join relatives, with reports that the Schengen Agreement is to be amended so the two can deal with the issue. (BBC) (Al Jazeera)Some Saudi Arabian women challenge a ban on female drivers, posting accounts and pictures of themselves driving automobiles. (The Guardian) (Gulf NEWS) (Sky News) (The New York Times) (Reuters)